  ["level_sitdown_marin.124"] = "Oh, dear! So, so many differences. Anaba Lee does a superb in-depth analysis of this in \"The Sociologist.\" It comes down to the Burgundy Group failing to understand that without going global, the mainstream ideology's apparatus crushes you.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.125"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.126"] = "Well, anarchist terrorists have existed for millennia. Even in this city, only a couple of decades ago, there were some attacks from such a group. They called themselves the Burgundy Riots because of those lovely red graffiti paint they used.  ",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.127"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.128"] = "I talked to my students the other day about this. It's not a singular ideology, but rather an umbrella of ideologies with a common anarchist backbone and divided into three branches. ",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.129"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.130"] = "Well, I couldn't help it. All my colleagues flaunted their fancy course names, so I had to step up my game. I couldn't just say that I teach \"ideology.\" So dull. That's why I came up with this name. It's wonderfully obtuse, isn't it? ",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.131"] = "They shrug and explain.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.132"] = "Oh my, little honey bee. You are just like my freshmen students, you know that? How could I choose between my babies? They are all wrong and right in their own unique ways, and that's why I love all of them. Except for Kant. He's just a dick. ",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.133"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.134"] = "What is a more wonderful thing to do than to corrupt the blank minds of little innocents with an understanding of their own ignorance, as well as the desperation that comes with an insatiable hunger for knowledge?",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.135"] = "They smile broadly.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.136"] = "And you are incredibly dull.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.137"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.138"] = "Don't take it personally, gingerbomb. I am just horrible with names. In this world dominated by identifiers with too many syllables, one must evolve or face a terrible social death.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.139"] = "They laugh.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.140"] = "Such a wonderful question! Technically? Just a coagulated system of normative axioms and theorems without epistemic function, which forms the basis of personal or societal policy.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.141"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.142"] = "Good conversations over a cup of coffee. Whatever I see, touch or hear. And the power of the human mind to believe that what they believe in, is actually real.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.143"] = "They state while taking a sip from their cup.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.144"] = "I don't know sweetheart, it is not me running an investigation on them. I guess, the usual methods: key people who influence their social nodes and the disgusting usage of subtle media nudges.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.145"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.146"] = "Well, everyone does it, so much we barely notice it. Do you remember that scandal about that tech and social media company Torpix, and their manipulation of people's online news recommendations? Imagine that is just the tip of the iceberg.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.147"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.148"] = "Well, darling, it is quite complex. Two of them fall someplace on the individualistic and collectivistic anarchism spectrum. The third one is a weird mixture with a lot of influences from international relations' realism. ",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.149"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.150"] = "Very well, sugar. Then tell me, what do you know about it?",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.151"] = "They nod lightly.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.152"] = "Well, any ideological fight is rhetorical in nature. Fight words with words, honey, not with guns. You just have to figure out what words will break the illusion of their words. You don't need me to spell it out for you.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.153"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.154"] = "Ok darling, I will spell it out for you. People need direction. Ideologies that don't offer that get hijacked and twisted until they do. This always leads to some centralization of power - eventually. Happens every time. The difference is only in form, not in function. ",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.155"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.156"] = "Oh darling, but you already know the answer. They are not special, you just need to show it to them, as well. The wonders of history, a flower that blooms with different colors, but the same shape, and which will shrivel - sooner or later. ",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.157"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.158"] = "Very well, cutie pie. Then tell me, what do you know about it?",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.159"] = "They nod lightly.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.160"] = "Yes, I did darling. Then tell me, what do you know about it?",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.161"] = "They nod lightly.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.162"] = "Oh, excuse me, stickypuff, I sometimes talk in academia gibberish. That's how you get tenure. What I mean is that folks just love agreeing with those they respect. So, if you get some influential people to preach for you, it's easy to spread your message. ",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.163"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.164"] = "Well, love, I do have a lot of professional respect for them; they play a great Blitzkrieg that may ultimately cost them the war. As some of my younger students say: mad balls, bro. ",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.165"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.166"] = "How do most couples stay together? By not talking about their issues and by projecting idealized scenarios of how everything will be fine. There is no logic-based reconciliation, as much as those 20th-century \"anarchists without adjectives\" would like us to believe.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.167"] = "They air quote. ",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.168"] = "Bravo, bravo! They do teach you some things at that police academy. Divide et Impera. ",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.169"] = "They applause lightly.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.170"] = "Angel, there are many arguments, but only some that have not already been tackled by propaganda. I can tell you my opinion of what would be most persuasive for believers of this ideology, but first, let's hear what you think. ",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.171"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.172"] = "Bravo! Yes darling, for those promised a world without serfdom, the thought of having their utopia destroyed by chains made out of customs and manipulative words is scary. ",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.173"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.174"] = "Yes and no. They think greed can be tackled through cultural conditioning. They are rather more scared of people that can use exactly that cultural conditioning to manipulate masses towards serfdom.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.175"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.176"] = "Not really... Half of the ideology is \"to each according to their needs\". What would be more persuasive is reminding them that a world in which the masses hold all the power, is also one that can easily be enslaved by charismatic leaders.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.177"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.178"] = "Sweetheart, you didn't need to read that defunct manuscript just for this meeting. ",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.179"] = "They state in a joyful tone.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.180"] = "Well darling, let me just take a sip out of this coffee made by your wonderful colleague, and I'll be right out of here.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.181"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.182"] = "Oh my, crunchysmile, if I knew this would be a date I would have put on some better clothes. ",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.183"] = "They joyfully tilt their head left and right.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.184"] = "Very well, darling. And later on, we shall talk about your department's ideology. ",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.185"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.186"] = "But isn't it obvious? They need to be stricken down by the mighty sword of justice!",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.187"] = "They chuckle briefly.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.188"] = "Dear, if I would tell you I believe in democracy, human rights, the free market and the national state, would that dissolve your suspicions? ",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.189"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.190"] = "Love, the definition of a car does not describe the difference between cars and a particular brand of cars. Same here.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.191"] = "They lightly shake their head before speaking. ",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.192"] = "Or as bad as a one-sentence definition can be.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.193"] = "They state with a dry smile.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.194"] = "Somebody has been reading their Zizek, I see. Well, I guess it comes down to the epistemological perspective from which we look at it, right? ",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.195"] = "They applaud lightly.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.196"] = "I don't think these people can be convinced that culture is the issue. However, if you tell them that the existence of modern weaponry, like tanks, could mean those lucky enough to have access to them will be able to conquer and enslave a weak majority, you may seed some doubt.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.197"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.198"] = "Well, it might work on some new recruits, but I expect that most would shrug it off by saying that nuclear bombings would be useless for small communities. However, using the logical argument with tanks as an example might work much better: a tool usable by the powerful to keep the weak masses weak.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.199"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.200"] = "A decent argument, but they could tell you that massive armies are hard to pull off. However, if you also mention that modern weaponry, like tanks, are very destructive and could be used to keep weak masses enslaved, you may really seed some doubt.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.201"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.202"] = "Well, sweetie, yes. It is left-anarchistic in nature. But other than that, I am certain there is a plethora of different sub-ideological beliefs held by different members. ",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.203"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.204"] = "Dear, if you want to debate with these people you must think about the argument which will be the most persuasive to them - the believers. I can tell you my opinion, but first, let's see what you think. ",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.205"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.206"] = "Honey, you really want to debate the indoctrinated? Then you need to think of the arguments they haven't heard and don't know how to tackle. I can tell you my opinion, but first, let's see what you think. ",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.207"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.208"] = "Well, dear, yes. It is anarchistic in nature. But other than that, I am certain there is a plethora of different sub-ideological beliefs held by different members. ",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.209"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.210"] = "Wonderful, I love playing spot the differences. Let's do it this way. You tell me what you think and I'll tell you if your assumption is correct or not. ",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.211"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.212"] = "What do you think is their main incompatibility? Let's put that deductive mind of yours to the test.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.213"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.214"] = "There are many, and only by thinking of them all do you begin to grasp which might be the hardest to solve. Go on, tell me which one would you choose and I'll tell you what I think. ",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.215"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.216"] = "Dear, do you need us to take a break?",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.217"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.218"] = "Anarcho-collectivism believes in a hierarchy-less, private-property-less and state-less society. In it, the common ownership of the means of production and a culture of empathy and social duty would allow for even the disenfranchised to prosper.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.219"] = "They speak loudly and gesture broadly.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.220"] = "Yes and no, sunshine. We all want harmony. Collectivist anarchists just believe that state-less, private property-less societies in which the means of production are commonly owned, create a culture of empathy and social duty that allows for even the disenfranchised to prosper.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.221"] = "They shake their head.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.222"] = "Exactly. They believe that only state-less, hierarchy-less, private property-less societies in which the means of production are commonly owned, create a culture of empathy and social duty that allows for even the disenfranchised to prosper.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.223"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.224"] = "Oh, but there are so many. Bakunin was the first to call for a violent revolution of the economically oppressed, instigated through terrorism which he called \"propaganda by the deed\". Then you can read Marx or Kropotkin, and so many others.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.225"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.226"] = "Well, the more successful ones were collectivists - but not anarchists - from the Bolshevik Revolution. There were, however, a few anarchists that succeeded in holding some territority for small amounts of time, such as the Spanish anarchists during the civil war in the 30's.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.227"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.228"] = "Bingo! For one to achieve happiness, they need to be able to be free and to do as they please with their body and their property as long as they respect the freedom of others. The state, and even democracy, limits this freedom. Only voluntary, fully consented transactions and agreements are moral. These also drive the economy to further prosperity.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.229"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.230"] = "Teachers hate lectures too, you know? Very well, it goes as such: individuals' needs are best achieved when no other individual or state restricts their freedom to use their body and property to pursue happiness. Only voluntary transactions are moral, and as such, they drive economic growth and social progress.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.231"] = "They shake their head.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.232"] = "Well, also this. But even today, you can be a hermit in the mountains. They rather believe that individuals' needs are best achieved when no other entity restricts their freedom to use their body and property to pursue happiness. Only voluntary, fully consented transactions and agreements are moral. These also drive the economy to further prosperity.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.233"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.234"] = "Fizzlepuff, there are so many of them. Start with William Godwin and Max Stirner, but to really understand it you also need to read a bit of Austrian School economists.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.235"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.236"] = "It is only the lazy that want answers and not questions. Well, dear, these anarcho-realists seem to believe that humans should always struggle for power and that the mainstream ideology grants the ruling class power in exchange for harmful comfort. Without such, people would organize in small warring communities, and in the long term, strengthening the species - in an evolutionary sense.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.237"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.238"] = "Precisely! These anarcho-realists seem to believe that humans should always struggle for power and that mainstream ideology grants the ruling class power in exchange for harmful comfort. Without such, people would organize in small warring communities, and in the long term, strengthening the species - in an evolutionary sense.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.239"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.240"] = "Not only that. These anarcho-realists seem to believe that humans should always struggle for power and that mainstream ideology grants the ruling class power in exchange for harmful comfort. Without such, people would organize in small warring communities, and in the long term, strengthening the species - in an evolutionary sense.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.241"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.242"] = "Well, this is the sub-ideology with the least history, but I guess you could read some insurrectionary anarchists like Wolfi Landstreicher, some anarcho-primitivists like John Zerzan, and obviously some international relations realists like Kissinger. ",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.243"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.244"] = "Don't worry sweetheart. Please, tell me, what do you want us to talk about? ",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.245"] = "They speak with a warm and joyful voice.",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.246"] = "Hey! ",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.247"] = "They do a small wave with their left hand. ",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.248"] = "Yes sunshine, I know of your little gift. Grateful, humbled. Hugs and smooches to all you lot. ",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.249"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.250"] = "Well sweetie, what I said was that it's not a singular ideology but rather an umbrella of ideologies with a common anarchist backbone and divided into three branches. ",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.251"] = "",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.252"] = "Very well. ",
  ["level_sitdown_marin.253"] = "",
